climbs.name: Mugwump
climbs.fa: David Kozak, John Marinaro, and Melinda Marinaro, 1983

content.description:
Do a rising traverse up and left from the start of

Endless Summer

and above the roof, and follow a 2" crack to the top. This is good fun and perhaps the best route at these cliffs.
content.protection: There is good protection with wires and up to 2" cams.

climbs.name: For Crying Out Loud
climbs.fa: David Kozak, John Marinaro, and Melinda Marinaro, 1983

content.description:
For Crying Out Loud is an ok route that goes right of

Endless Summer

after about 10 feet.
content.protection: Wires and cams to 1" and no fixed anchor.
content.location:
Climb first ten feet of

Endless Summer

, then go right, and follow a 1" crack to the top.

content.description: Climb up the distinctive black streak just right of a large section of whitish rock. This is a fun route.
content.protection: There is good pro with wires and small cams.
content.location:
The route is 40 to 50 feet right of

Blues Incognition

dihedral.

content.description: Climb the sustained V dihedral found about 30 feet right of the southwest face of the rock.
content.protection: Nuts and cams. There is no fixed anchor.
content.location: Start in the obvious V dihedral.
